io.nats.client

Interface SyncSubscription

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable, Subscription

    public interface SyncSubscription
extends Subscription
    A client uses an SyncSubscription object to receive messages from a subject synchronously.

    • Method Detail

      • nextMessage

        Message nextMessage()
             throws IOException
        Receive the next message that becomes available for this Subscription, waiting if necessary until a Message becomes available.
        Returns:
        the next message produced for this subscription, or return null if the Connection is closed concurrently.
        Throws:
        IOException - if an I/O error prevents message delivery
        IllegalStateException - if the Subscription has been removed (unsubscribed)
        IOException - if the Subscription's has been unsubscribed due to reaching its autoUnsubscribe limit.
        See Also:
        Subscription.autoUnsubscribe(int)

      • nextMessage

        Message nextMessage(long timeout)
             throws IOException,
                    TimeoutException
        Receive the next Message that arrives for this Subscription within the specified timeout interval.
        Parameters:
        timeout - the timeout value (in milliseconds)
        Returns:
        the next message produced for this subscription, or return null if timeout expires
        Throws:
        IOException - if an I/O error prevents message delivery
        TimeoutException - if the timeout expires before a message becomes available
        IllegalStateException - if the Subscription has been removed (unsubscribed)
        IOException - if the Subscription's has been unsubscribed due to reaching its autoUnsubscribe limit.
        See Also:
        nextMessage(long, TimeUnit), Subscription.autoUnsubscribe(int)

      • nextMessage

        Message nextMessage(long timeout,
                    TimeUnit unit)
             throws IOException,
                    TimeoutException
        Receive the next Message that arrives for this Subscription within the specified timeout interval.
        Parameters:
        timeout - how long to wait before giving up, in units of unit
        unit - the timeout value
        Returns:
        the next message produced for this subscription, or return null if timeout expires
        Throws:
        IOException - if an I/O error prevents message delivery
        TimeoutException - if the timeout expires before a message becomes available
        IllegalStateException - if the Subscription has been removed (unsubscribed)
        IOException - if the Subscription's has been unsubscribed due to reaching its autoUnsubscribe limit.
